1) Create a new class  ArithmeticOperators and add a main method

➕ Addition Example – Total Fruits:
-Create two variables:  apples and bananas.
-Add (+) them to find the totalNumberOfFruits then print out

➖ Subtraction Example – Wallet After Purchase:
-Create two variables: wallet and price.
-Subtract(-) price from wallet and store the result in remaining. and print out.

✖️ Multiplication Example – Items in Boxes:
-Create two int variables: boxes and itemsPerBox.
-Multiply them to get totalItems then print out

➗ Division Example – Time per Task:
-Create two int variables: totalMinutes and tasks.
-Divide totalMinutes by tasks to get minutesPerTask then print out.

➗ Modulus/Remainder Example – Leftover Chocolates:
-Create two int variables: chocolates and friends.
-Use % to calculate how many chocolates are leftover after sharing then print out

From totalSeconds calculate minutes and remainingSeconds:
-Display in this format:
-In 550 seconds - there are 9 minutes and 10 seconds
________________________________________________

2) Create a new class BMICalculator and add a main method
    Program to calculate Body Mass Index
    Formula metric system => BMI = weight / (height * height)

    1. Declare and initialize double weight and height variables
    2. Calculate BMI value using above formula and assign to double BMI variable
    3. Print out the result as below format:
    The Body Mass Index (BMI) is 33.33 kg/m2
________________________________________________

3) TipOptions [variables, operators, concatenation]

Declare and assign the following variables
   String food (list of any 3 food items),
   Assign price for each item - item1Price, item2Price, item3Price
   Calculate total (amount you owe) includes all 3 item prices plus 5% tax

show the receipt of all the items and total cost of the bill
then display 3 tip options and how much they would cost.
show the tip for 10%, 18% and 25%
