7) Create a new class ComparisonOperators and add main method

Check if your test score is greater than the passing score:
-declare int testScore with value 85
-declare int passMark with value 50
-use > to compare and store result in a boolean variable passed then print it

Check if the room temperature is below freezing:
-declare int temperature with value -2
-use < to compare with 0 and store result in a boolean isFreezing then print it

Check if your age is enough to vote (18 or older):
-declare int age with value 18
-use >= to check if age is at least 18(canVote) then print result

Check if luggage weight is within 23kg airline limit:
-declare int luggageWeight with value 20
-use <= to check(isWithinLimit) and print result

Check if the entered PIN is correct:
-declare int enteredPin with value 1234
-declare int correctPin with value 1234
-use == to compare(isCorrect) then print the result

Check if a seat is not already reserved:
-declare int selectedSeat with value 22
-declare int reservedSeat with value 15
-use != to compare(seatAvailable) and print the result
________________________________________________
8) Create a new class LogicalOperators and add main method

Check if you can unlock a device (must know password and have fingerprint):
-declare boolean knowsPassword with value true
-declare boolean hasFingerprint with value true
-use && to check both conditions then print result

Check if you can get a discount (if you're a student OR a senior):
-declare boolean isStudent with value false
-declare boolean isSenior with value true
-use || to check either condition then print result

Check if it is NOT both sunny (so you stay in):
-declare boolean isSunny with value true
-use ! to check if it’s NOT both sunny, then print result
________________________________________________

8) Create a new class ShirtSelection and add main method

Only buy shirt if (size is medium) and (color is blue or tan) and (price between $10 - $30)
-declare char size with value M
-declare String color with value blue
-declare double price with value 15
-use logical operators to assign boolean willBuy then print out result

9) Create new class PrimitiveCasting and add main method

You are putting small primitive to larger one:
- declare byte variable small and assign 100
- declare int variable large and assign small
- print out values

An item costs $5, and you want to calculate price with tax as a double.
- declare int variable itemPrice and assign 5
- declare double variable finalPrice and assign itemPrice
- print out values and observe decimals

User’s account balance is rounded to the nearest whole dollar for display.
- declare double variable balance and assign 1250.75
- declare int variable roundedBalance and assign balance with casting
- print out rounded balance

A vending machine only stores item codes as bytes:
- declare integer variable itemCode and assign 120
- declare byte variable storedCode and assign itemCode with casting
- print out stored code